dients" content="50ml maple syrup">50ml <a href="/glossary/maple-syrup" class="ingredients-list__glossary-link" data-tooltip-content="#ingredients-glossary &gt; article" data-tooltip-width="350" data-tooltip-hide-delay="200" data-tooltip-flyout="true">maple syrup</a><span class="ingredients-list__glossary-element" id="ingredients-glossary"><article id="node-6458491" role="main" class="node node-glossary-item node-teaser node-teaser clearfix main row grid-padding"><div class="node-image"> <a href="/glossary/maple-syrup"><img src="//www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/styles/bbcgf_thumbnail_search/public/glossary-item/glossary-image/2017/03/maple-syrup_700.jpg?itok=l8svBQRE" width="100" height="100" alt="Maple syrup" title="Maple syrup" /></a></div><h2 class="node-title node-glossary-title"><a href="/glossary/maple-syrup">Maple syrup</a></h2> <span class="fonetic text-style-alt">may-pul sir-rup</span><p><span style="line-height:107%">The rising spring sap of a number of varieties of maple tree</span>â€¦</p> </article></span></li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="500g jumbo rolled oats">500g jumbo rolled <a href="/glossary/oats" class="ingredients-list__glossary-link" data-tooltip-content="#ingredients-glossary--2 &gt; article" data-tooltip-width="350" data-tooltip-hide-delay="200" data-tooltip-flyout="true">oats</a><span class="ingredients-list__glossary-element" id="ingredients-glossary--2"><article id="node-6909446" role="main" class="node node-glossary-item node-teaser node-teaser clearfix main row grid-padding"><div class="node-image"> <a href="/glossary/oats"><img src="//www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/styles/bbcgf_thumbnail_search/public/glossary-item/glossary-image/2017/11/oats.jpg?itok=bOLGFGtp" width="100" height="100" alt="Two piles of oats" title="Oats definition" /></a></div><h2 class="node-title node-glossary-title"><a href="/glossary/oats">Oats</a></h2> <span class="fonetic text-style-alt">ohtz</span><p>Oats are processed by rolling (steamed and pressed) or steel-cutting (cut into pieces). There isâ€¦</p> </article></span></li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="100g flaked almond">100g flaked almond</li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="50g pine nut">50g pine nut</li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="100g puffed rice">100g puffed <a href="/glossary/rice" class="ingredients-list__glossary-link" data-tooltip-content="#ingredients-glossary--3 &gt; article" data-tooltip-width="350" data-tooltip-hide-delay="200" data-tooltip-flyout="true">rice</a><span class="ingredients-list__glossary-element" id="ingredients-glossary--3"><article id="node-6030031" role="main" class="node node-glossary-item node-teaser node-teaser clearfix main row grid-padding"><div class="node-image"> <a href="/glossary/rice"><img src="//www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/styles/bbcgf_thumbnail_search/public/glossary-item/glossary-image/2016/08/rice.jpg?itok=s7RRNgFG" width="100" height="100" alt="Rice" title="Rice" /></a></div><h2 class="node-title node-glossary-title"><a href="/glossary/rice">Rice</a></h2> <span class="fonetic text-style-alt">r-eye-s</span><p>Rice is a grain, the seed of a type of grass, which is the most widely grown and the mostâ€¦</p> </article></span></li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="2 tbsp sesame seeds">2 tbsp sesame seeds</li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="50g each sultanasand raisins">50g each sultanas and raisins</li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="85g each dried cranberries, dried cherries, chopped dried dates and chopped dried apricots">85g each dried cranberries, dried cherries, chopped dried <a href="/glossary/date" class="ingredients-list__glossary-link" data-tooltip-content="#ingredients-glossary--4 &gt; article" data-tooltip-width="350" data-tooltip-hide-delay="200" data-tooltip-flyout="true">dates</a> and chopped dried apricots<span class="ingredients-list__glossary-element" id="ingredients-glossary--4"><article id="node-260036" role="main" class="node node-glossary-item node-teaser node-teaser clearfix main row grid-padding"><div class="node-image"> <a href="/glossary/date"><img src="//www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/styles/bbcgf_thumbnail_search/public/glossary/dates-resized.jpg?itok=5xzC25Yi" width="100" height="100" alt="Dates" title="Dates" /></a></div><h2 class="node-title node-glossary-title"><a href="/glossary/date">Date</a></h2> <span class="fonetic text-style-alt">da-ate</span><p>Dates are one of the oldest cultivated fruits - it's thought that they were a staple part ofâ€¦</p> </article></span></li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="50g dried coconutshavings (find these at juliangraves.com and healthfood shops)">50g dried <a href="/glossary/coconut" class="ingredients-list__glossary-link" data-tooltip-content="#ingredients-glossary--5 &gt; article" data-tooltip-width="350" data-tooltip-hide-delay="200" data-tooltip-flyout="true">coconut</a> shavings (find these at juliangraves.com and healthfood shops)<span class="ingredients-list__glossary-element" id="ingredients-glossary--5"><article id="node-260721" role="main" class="node node-glossary-item node-teaser node-teaser clearfix main row grid-padding"><div class="node-image"> <a href="/glossary/coconut"><img src="//www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/styles/bbcgf_thumbnail_search/public/glossary/coconut.jpeg?itok=BvLPIApY" width="100" height="100" alt="Coconut" title="Coconut" /></a></div><h2 class="node-title node-glossary-title"><a href="/glossary/coconut">Coconut</a></h2> <span class="fonetic text-style-alt">koe-koe-nut</span><p>A large hairy, brown nut that grows on the coconut tree, found throughout the world'sâ€¦</p> </article></span></li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="Greek yogurtand raspberries, to serve">Greek yogurt and raspberries, to serve</li></ul></div></div> </section> <section id="recipe-method" class="responsive-tabs__pane"><h2 class="responsive-tabs__pane-title">Method</h2><div class="method"><ol class="method__list"><li class="method__item" itemprop="recipeInstructions"><p>Heat oven to 160C/fan 140C/gas 3. Heat the oil, honey and maple syrup together in a pan. Mix the oats, almonds, pine nuts, puffed rice and sesame seeds in a large mixing bowl. Pour over the honey mix, stir well to coat, then tip onto a large baking tray. Bake for 15 mins until everything is golden and crisp.</p></li><li class="method__item" itemprop="recipeInstructions"><p>Take the tray from the oven, leave to cool, then break up any big clumps. Mix together with the dried fruit and coconut shavings. Serve with Greek yogurt and fresh raspberries. The rest of the granola can be stored in a sealed jar and enjoyed over the next 2 weeks.</p></li></ol></div> <footer class="recipe-info"><div class="recipe-info__publication">Recipe from Good Food magazine, <a href="/search/recipes/date/1241132400" class="text-style-alt">May 2009</a></div> <a class="recipe-info__magazine-ad" href=" https://www.buysubscriptions.com/print/bbc-good-food-magazine-subscription?promo=GFBS718&style=Brand&utm_medium=brandsite&utm_source=bbcgoodfood.com&utm_campaign=recipe_GFBS718_Brand&utm_content=recipe-banner" rel="external" onclick="Drupal.GFAnalytics.trackEvent(['Magazines', 'subscribe', 'Recipe' ])"> <img src="https://www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/magazine/gf_aug18_337x109.jpg" alt="BBC GoodFood Magazine" /> </a> </footer> </section></div></div> <section id="block-bbcgf-search-views-bbcgf-cc-rel-recipes" class="section-box section-box--you-may-also-like"> <header class="section-box__header"><h2 class="section-box__title">You may also like</h2> </header><div class="section-box__content"><div class="carousel"><div class="flexslider type-1" data-type="1"><ul class="slides"><li cla